<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Deck1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Deck,</orth> subst. 1) the covering or floor of a ship: <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.197" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 197</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.1.94" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 1, 94</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.2.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 2, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.3.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 3, 11</bibl>. Per. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.0." default="NO" valid="yes">III Prol. 59</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.1.57" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.1.115" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 115</bibl>.<lb />2) a pack of cards: <cit><quote>whiles he thought to steal the single ten, the king was slily fingered from the d.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.1.44" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C V, 1, 44</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>